<dl id="n06154p"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06154p">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06154p"> 154(p)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> resurrection of / damnation <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n06154p"><li>FW 62.19 </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/lexc.htm#n06154p">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/l39c.htm#n06154p">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n06154p">MS BL 47471b-10v</ms> </li><li>JJA 45:151 <a name="c20d" href="../../FF/fdra/cda.htm#c20d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/c/c20d.htm#n06154p">Draft: I.3&sect;2.0</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">ELEVENTH ARTICLE. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> THE RESURRECTION BODY will be a glorious body; &ldquo;we shall also bear the image of the Heavenly.&rdquo; &ldquo;We shall be like Him.&rdquo; The resurrection of the righteous is called by our Lord &ldquo;the resurrection of life;&rdquo; the resurrection of the wicked is called &ldquo;<mark>the resurrection of damnation</mark>.&rdquo; <small> Anonymous, <a name="ATCC" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ATCC"><cite title="source">Analysis of the Church Catechism</cite></a> (1879) 25-6</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
